docs.abstract: Investors are worried about how much companies are spending on artificial intelligence, but the tech giant is sure that its efforts will pay off.
docs.snippet: Investors are worried about how much companies are spending on artificial intelligence, but the tech giant is sure that its efforts will pay off.
docs.lead_paragraph: The technology sector is facing another rough patch, after Microsoft reported mixed quarterly earnings and its shares tumbled. The company’s results are fueling more concern among investors about whether hefty spending on artificial intelligence will pay off, and how long that might take.

headline.main: Why Microsoft’s Earnings Miss Won’t Stall the A.I. Boom

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: The House Homeland Security Committee called on the chief executive of the cybersecurity firm to testify on the disruption.
docs.snippet: The House Homeland Security Committee called on the chief executive of the cybersecurity firm to testify on the disruption.
docs.lead_paragraph: A Congressional committee called on the chief executive of CrowdStrike to testify at a hearing about its role in a tech outage that roiled the global economy, in one of the first attempts to hold the cybersecurity company responsible.

headline.main: Congress Calls for Tech Outage Hearing to Grill CrowdStrike C.E.O.
headline.print_headline: Congress; Panel Wants CrowdStrike To Testify on Tech Outage

docs.abstract: The company said it effectively got all of the electricity it used last year from sources that did not produce greenhouse gas emissions. Some experts have faulted the company’s calculations.
docs.snippet: The company said it effectively got all of the electricity it used last year from sources that did not produce greenhouse gas emissions. Some experts have faulted the company’s calculations.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon announced on Wednesday that effectively all of the electricity its operations used last year came from sources that did not produce greenhouse gas emissions. But some experts have criticized the method the company uses to make that determination as being too lenient.

headline.main: Amazon Says It Reached a Climate Goal Seven Years Early
headline.print_headline: Amazon Says It Reached Climate Goal

byline.original: By Ivan Penn and Eli Tan

docs.abstract: A massive outage related to a security update by CrowdStrike, a cybersecurity company, crippled airlines and other businesses on Friday.
docs.snippet: A massive outage related to a security update by CrowdStrike, a cybersecurity company, crippled airlines and other businesses on Friday.
docs.lead_paragraph: An outage that crippled businesses around the world turned many Microsoft computers into bricks overnight.

headline.main: What to Do if Your Computer Is Affected by the Microsoft Outage
headline.print_headline: So Your Computer Is Suddenly Useless. Here Is What to Try After It Crashes.

byline.original: By David McCabe and Kate Conger

docs.abstract: A problem with Microsoft’s Azure system also hit check-in and booking systems at Allegiant and Sun Country Airlines.
docs.snippet: A problem with Microsoft’s Azure system also hit check-in and booking systems at Allegiant and Sun Country Airlines.
docs.lead_paragraph: Frontier Airlines briefly grounded all flights on Thursday amid a major outage in Microsoft networks, which also knocked out some computer systems at low-cost carriers Allegiant Air and Sun Country Airlines.

headline.main: Frontier Airlines Briefly Grounds All Flights Amid Microsoft Outage

docs.abstract: CrowdStrike’s cybersecurity software is used by scores of industries, including airlines, hospitals and retailers, to prevent hacks and data breaches.
docs.snippet: CrowdStrike’s cybersecurity software is used by scores of industries, including airlines, hospitals and retailers, to prevent hacks and data breaches.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Friday morning, flights were canceled, broadcasters went off air, trains didn’t run and medical procedures were delayed around the world. Frustrated workers were confronted with blue computer screens and no obvious way to get back online.

headline.print_headline: Cybersecurity Takes a Blow By the Hand Of a Protector

byline.original: By Kate Conger and Claire Moses
